<h2>Part 2: Video Ad Production: Complete Process from Script to Editing</h2>
<h3>2.1 Script Structure for Viral Video Ads</h3>
<p>High-performing video ads follow a <strong>"Hook-Value-Action" three-layer structure</strong>:</p>
<p><strong>Layer 1: Hook (0-3 seconds)</strong></p>
<p>Opening must create visual impact or cognitive conflict. Common techniques include:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Pain Point Direct Approach</strong>: Display scenes of users' daily life struggles</li>
<li><strong>Counter-intuitive Display</strong>: Exaggerated product effect demonstrations</li>
<li><strong>Suspense Setting</strong>: Pose questions without immediate answers</li>
<li><strong>Trending Elements</strong>: Leverage hot topics, quotes, memes</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Layer 2: Value Presentation (3-15 seconds)</strong></p>
<p>Central product/service value concentration. Adopt the <strong>"one selling point every 3 seconds"</strong> rhythm, covering maximum 4 core selling points. Forms can combine:</p>
<ul>
<li>Product feature demonstrations</li>
<li>Usage scenario simulations</li>
<li>Real user testimonials (require real names or verifiable information)</li>
<li>Data backing (third-party certifications, user review screenshots)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Layer 3: Call to Action (Final 5 seconds)</strong></p>
<p>Clear purchase/conversion guidance. Considerations:</p>
<ul>
<li>CTA button needs visual prominence, contrasting with overall color palette</li>
<li>Concise and powerful copy: "Shop Now," "Claim Free Trial," "Get Started"</li>
<li>Price information can be reiterated here, combined with promotional tags</li>
</ul>
