<h3>2.3 Production Methods for UGC-Style Creatives</h3>
<p>In 2024, Meta's algorithm clearly favors <strong>native, authentic</strong> content. UGC-style creatives average 22% lower CPM than professionally produced content, yet achieve 15% higher conversion rates.</p>
<p><strong>Low-Cost UGC Creative Production Guide:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Equipment Selection</strong>: iPhone 14 Pro or above, supporting 4K 30fps</li>
<li><strong>Lighting Requirements</strong>: Prioritize natural light, avoid direct sunlight, choose overcast outdoor or window scattered light</li>
<li><strong>Sound Processing</strong>: Retain ambient sound, add light background music (with proper licensing), voice needs clarity</li>
<li><strong>Editing Style</strong>: Avoid over-packaging, retain "roughness," add lightweight subtitles and transitions</li>
<li><strong>Talent Selection</strong>: Non-professional models preferred, natural expressions, avoid overacting</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Case Study:</strong> A DTC beauty brand increased ad campaign ROAS from 2.1 to 3.8 through their "Real User Reviews" series. Core strategy: recruited real users to film "unboxing + application + review" three-part videos, entirely unscripted, only providing product core selling point lists as reference.</p>
<h2>Part 3: Copywriting: The Conversion Copywriting Pyramid Model</h2>
<h3>3.1 Five Psychological Drivers for High-Conversion Copy</h3>
<p><strong>1. Urgency</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>"Only 3 days left," "Low stock alert," "Today only"</li>
<li>Data: Urgency-driven copy increases CTR by 19%</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>2. Uniqueness</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>"Worldwide first launch," "Exclusive patent," "Limited custom"</li>
<li>Data: Uniqueness claims increase ad relevance scores by an average of 1.2 points</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>3. Utility</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Clearly show specific problems the product solves</li>
<li>"Save 50% time," "One-click solution," "Beginner-friendly"</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>4. Intimacy</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Use "you" instead of formal "you," reducing distance</li>
<li>"We understand your struggle," "Designed for users like you"</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>5. Social Proof</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>"Choice of 100,000+ users," "98% positive rating"</li>
<li>"Celebrity favorite," "Influencer recommended"</li>
</ul>
